com.k2.Expressions.evaluators

Class ParamterOrObjectEvaluator<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.k2.Expressions.evaluators.SimpleParameterEvaluator
      • com.k2.Expressions.evaluators.GenericEvaluator<E>
        • com.k2.Expressions.evaluators.ParamterOrObjectEvaluator<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of the object that provides values for getter expressions.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Evaluator, GetterEvaluator<E>, ParameterEvaluator

    public class ParamterOrObjectEvaluator<E>
extends GenericEvaluator<E>
implements Evaluator, ParameterEvaluator, GetterEvaluator<E>
    This class extends the generic evaluator and allows the values returned for parameter expressions to be fulfilled by values from the generic evaluators value source and the values set on the evaluator. It also allows getter expressions to be fulfilled by set parameter values. If a value is available from the set parameter values then that value is returned for either a suitable parameter expression or a getter expression. If a value is not available from the set parameter values then the set generic valuators value source is inspected for a suitable value for the requested parameter or getter expression.
    Author:
    simon
